Class BoardFacade

java.lang.Object
ui.BoardFacade
All Implemented Interfaces:
BoardView
public class BoardFacade extends Object implements BoardView
Facade that bridges the mutable Board model with the BoardView interface.

Exposes both the read-only board view used by the UI and limited write operations through trySet(int, int, int). The facade delegates all reads and writes directly to the underlying Board, which maintains both cell values and their "given" status.

    • hasUniqueSolution

      public boolean hasUniqueSolution()
      Determines whether the current puzzle has exactly one valid solution.

      This method queries the Solver to check whether a solved board has been computed and that the number of identified solutions is exactly one. It performs no solving itself.

      Specified by:
      hasUniqueSolution in interface BoardView
